name: fahrenheit

name: gramsPerHectarePerDay

name: gramsPerMeterSquaredPerYear

name: gramsPerOneQuarterMeterSquared

name: kilogramsPerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: kilograms per meter squared per second

name: Link_Clarke
description: This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be accurate.

name: microEinsteinsPerSquareMeter

description: milliliters of solution per total volume

name: nominalDay
description: one day excluding leap seconds, 86400 seconds

name: nominalHour
description: one hour excluding leap seconds, 3600 seconds

name: nominalLeapYear
description: one 366 day year excluding leap seconds, 31622400 seconds

name: nominalMinute
description: one minute excluding leap seconds, 60 seconds

name: nominalWeek
description: one day excluding leap seconds, 604800 seconds

name: nominalYear
description: one year excluding leap seconds and leap days, 31536000 seconds

name: numberPerMilliliter
description: number of particles or organisms per milliliter of solution

name: numberPerSquareCentimeterPerHour

name: partsPerMillion

name: partsPerThousand
description: ratio of two quantities as parts per thousand (1:1000)

name: percent
description: ratio of two quantities as percent composition (1:100)

description: pCi/g = 1E-12 Curies per gram of sample, equal to 2.22 radioactive disintegrations per minute per gram of sample

description: picomoles per liter of solution per hour (concentration flux)

name: radian
description: 2 pi radians comprise a unit circle.

name: serialDateNumberYear0000

description: siemens per meter (electrolytic conductivity of a solution)

name: tonnePerHectare
description: metric ton or tonne per hectare

name: Yard_Indian
description: This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be accurate.

name: Yard_Sears
description: This is an ESRI unit and the multiplier comes from ESRI. It may not be accurate.

name: meterSquared
description: area, meter squared from the LTER unit dictionary

name: micromolePerMeterSquared
description: commonly used for integrated concentration of chemical constituents in natural water bodies

name: permil
description: permil is a shorthand way of saying parts per thousand parts. values must have the same dimensions.

name: picomolePerLiterPerHour
description: picomoles per liter of solution per hour (concentration flux)

name: hectoPascal
description: SI unit for atmospheric pressure, equivalent in magnitude to millibar

name: milligramPerMeterCubed
description: concentration unit, sometimes used for pigments in natural waters.same magnitude as microgramPerLiter

name: milligramPerMeterCubedPerDay
description: a volumetric flux unit. often used for a primary production rate, e.g., for a parcel of water. Often is specific to an element, e.g., carbon

name: micromolePerLiter
description: commonly used for concentration of some chemical constituents of natural water bodies, e.g., nutrients. It has the same magnitude as micromolar, but micromolar can only be used for a dissolved constituent

name: milligramPerLiter
description: concentration unit, sometimes used for pigments in natural waters

name: microgramPerLiter
description: concentration unit. Based on the dimensions (mass/volume), the unitType is probably density, but this would be misleading, so it is left NULL here.

name: microeinsteinPerMeterSquaredPerSecond
description: PAR irradiance unit, Seabird 911. 1Ein = energy of 1 mole photons

name: microeinsteinPerCentimeterSquaredPerSecond
description: PAR irradiance unit, 1Ein = energy of 1 mole photons

name: kilogramPerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: areal primary production rate, may apply to DW, or to element content, e.g., Carbon or Nitrogen

name: siemensPerCentimeter
description: conductivity unit, seawater, A siemems is equal to one ampere per volt.

name: microequivalentPerLiter
description: concentration of charge (on dissolved ions). A single multiplier to SI is not possible, since conversion includes valence of ion, which can vary

name: micromolePerKilogram
description: a concentration unit used in oceanography. volume changes with depth, but mass does not. Not sure what the unitType should be.

name: milligramPerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: an areal flux unit. often used for a primary production rate, e.g., for an integrated water column. May have context of dry weight, or specific to an element, e.g., carbon

name: molePerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: an areal flux unit, moles (of an element) per day.

name: microgramPerMeterSquared
description: used for integrated concentration of chemical constituents when measured by weight, e.g., pigments.

name: biomassDensityUnitPerAbundanceUnit
description: a ratio of two other units

name: numberPer85CentimeterSquaredPerDay
description: number of organisms (things) per area of 85 cm squared per day

name: microMolesPerLiter
description: µM = µmoles per liter of solution

name: dimensionless
description: a designation asserting the absence of an associated unit

name: acre
description: 1 acre = 4046.8564 square meters or 1 hectare = 2.4710 acres

name: millimolePerMeterSquaredPerDay
description: millimole per square meter per day

name: milligramPerGramPerHour
description: specific rate, used for production and respiration
